query:
SELECT 
  'Journeys' as tableName,
  COUNT(*) as totalRecords
FROM journeys
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Journey Days',
  COUNT(*)
FROM journeyDays
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Conversations',
  COUNT(*)
FROM conversations
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Conversation Messages',
  COUNT(*)
FROM conversationMessages
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Embeddings',
  COUNT(*)
FROM embeddings
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Users',
  COUNT(*)
FROM users
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Journal Entries',
  COUNT(*)
FROM journalEntries
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Paradoxes',
  COUNT(*)
FROM paradoxes
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Life Experiments',
  COUNT(*)
FROM life_experiments
UNION ALL
SELECT 'Micro Retreats',
  COUNT(*)
FROM micro_retreats;
